-- Scottish support for independence rises to 49 percent, Ipsos MORI poll 
-- 
-- Wed Sep 17, 2014 12:21PM EDT
-- None



EDINBURGH, Sept 17 (Reuters) - Scottish support for independence has risen to 49 percent, an Ipsos MORI poll showed on the eve of a referendum that could break the United Kingdom apart.

The Ipsos MORI poll showed support for Scotland staying in the United Kingdom on 51 percent, the STV news broadcaster said.